        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you service the ice maker inside my built-in refrigerator?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, integrated ice makers in Classic BI units (BI-36U, BI-42S, BI-48S) and Designer freezer columns (IC-36FI, IC-24FI, IC-18FI) share architecture with the standalone UC models but are mounted inside the freezer compartment. Most common issues mirror standalone: water inlet valve, frozen fill tube, failed module, failed ice-level sensor. Module replacement $320–$450 is the most common repair. We service these during the same visits as refrigerator/freezer work, one dispatch handles both."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
